*Mounting Google drive as a Virtual drive on ubuntu (Virtual storage): OcamlFuse*

https://github.com/astrada/google-drive-ocamlfuse

sudo add-apt-repository ppa:alessandro-strada/ppa
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install google-drive-ocamlfuse
google-drive-ocamlfuse -headless -label manie -id 1026579755882-ftce7bi3vmrm26rhcc5paatm8eapnd18.apps.googleusercontent.com -secret LrVUNPekOvCxTvwPQ-I-MVOZ

Now we could see the label name 'manie' is created in the path '/root/.gdfuse/manie'
Create your 'Gdrive' folder on any location (either root/xxx) or (/home/admin/web/s1.paysofts.com/public_html/gdrive)
Then the below command will configure the path from the profile of 'manie'
google-drive-ocamlfuse -label manie /home/admin/web/s2.paysofts.com/public_html/gdrive
Now  we have the Gdrive folder, which will auto-sync all the files from the Gdrive account.

To unmount the filesystem, issue this command:
umount /home/admin/web/s2.paysofts.com/public_html/gdrive
